The following stocks may rise or fall
in  South Africa . Symbols are in parentheses and prices are from
the last close.  The FTSE/JSE Africa All Share Index dropped 124.80, or 0.4
percent, to 31,794.13 in Johannesburg, giving a decline of 0.5
percent for the week.  African Bank Investments Ltd. (ABL)  : The financial-
services provider releases first-half earnings. The stock fell
1.29 rand, or 3.6 percent, to 34.20 rand.  Verimark Holdings Ltd. (VMK)  : The retailer of fitness
equipment and household goods reports full-year earnings. Its
shares gained 5 cents, or 3 percent, to 1.70 rand.  Famous Brands Ltd. (FBR)  : The countryâ€™s biggest fast-
food franchise owner posts full-year earnings. Famous added 8
cents, or 0.2 percent, to 43.81 rand.  Lewis Group Ltd. (LEW)  : The furniture and electrical-
goods retailer posts full-year earnings. Lewis fell 90 cents, or
1.2 percent, to 76.60 rand.  The following stocks begin trading without the right to
